(30, 'Where do your parents live?', 'where-do-your-parents-live', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-30.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/30.mp3', 'Jason', 'Melissa', '["Hi Melissa, are you going home this weekend?","No, not this weekend. I have too much work to do","Where do your parents live?","My father lives in Washington DC","How about your mother?","My mother died two years ago","Oh, I am sorry to hear that. Is your father still working?","No, he\\u2019s retired","Do you have any family here?","Yes, two of my cousins live here and my aunt and uncle live about 30 miles from here","Do you have any brothers or sisters?","Yes, I have two brothers who live in New York and a sister who lives in Boston","Do you see them a lot","Not as much as I\\u2019d like to. Usually just on holidays like Thanksgiving and Christmas"]', '["Ch\\u00e0o Melissa, b\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd v\\u1ec1 nh\\u00e0 cu\\u1ed1i tu\\u1ea7n n\\u00e0y kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng, cu\\u1ed1i tu\\u1ea7n n\\u00e0y th\\u00ec kh\\u00f4ng. T\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 nhi\\u1ec1u vi\\u1ec7c ph\\u1ea3i l\\u00e0m qu\\u00e1","B\\u1ed1 m\\u1eb9 b\\u1ea1n s\\u1ed1ng \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","B\\u1ed1 t\\u00f4i s\\u1ed1ng \\u1edf Washington DC","C\\u00f2n m\\u1eb9 b\\u1ea1n?","M\\u1eb9 t\\u00f4i m\\u1ea5t c\\u00e1ch \\u0111\\u00e2y hai n\\u0103m r\\u1ed3i","\\u00d4, t\\u00f4i r\\u1ea5t ti\\u1ebfc nghe nh\\u01b0 v\\u1eady. B\\u1ed1 b\\u1ea1n c\\u00f2n \\u0111i l\\u00e0m kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng, \\u00f4ng \\u1ea5y v\\u1ec1 h\\u01b0u r\\u1ed3i","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 h\\u1ecd h\\u00e0ng \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2y kh\\u00f4ng?","C\\u00f3, hai ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi trong s\\u1ed1 anh ch\\u1ecb em h\\u1ecd c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i s\\u1ed1ng \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2y v\\u00e0 c\\u00f4 ch\\u00fa t\\u00f4i s\\u1ed1ng c\\u00e1ch \\u0111\\u00e2y kho\\u1ea3ng 30 d\\u1eb7m","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 anh ch\\u1ecb em g\\u00ec kh\\u00f4ng?","C\\u00f3, t\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 2 ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi anh (em) s\\u1ed1ng \\u1edf New York v\\u00e0 m\\u1ed9t ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi ch\\u1ecb (em g\\u00e1i) s\\u1ed1ng \\u1edf Boston","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u01b0\\u1eddng g\\u1eb7p h\\u1ecd kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c nhi\\u1ec1u nh\\u01b0 t\\u00f4i mu\\u1ed1n.Th\\u01b0\\u1eddng ch\\u1ec9 v\\u00e0o nh\\u1eefng ng\\u00e0y ngh\\u1ec9 nh\\u01b0 L\\u1ec5 T\\u1ea1 \\u01a0n v\\u00e0 Gi\\u00e1ng Sinh"]', '1', '30', '2017-08-03 19:48:13', '2017-08-03 19:48:13'),
(31, 'Can you help me find a few things?', 'can-you-help-me-find-a-few-things', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-31.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/31.mp3', 'Matt', 'Anna', '["I can\\u2019t find my glasses and I can\\u2019t see anything. Can you help me find a few things?","No problem. What are you looking for?","My laptop, do you see it?","Yes, your laptop is on the chair","Where\\u2019s my book?","Which one?","The dictionary","It\\u2019s under the table","Where\\u2019s my pencil?","There\\u2019s a pencil in front of the lamp","That\\u2019s not a pencil. That\\u2019s a pen","Oh, sorry. There is a pencil behind the cup","How about my backpack? Do you know where that is?","It\\u2019s in between the wall and the bed","Where are my shoes?","They\\u2019re on the left side of the TV","I don\\u2019t see them","Sorry, I made a mistake. They\\u2019re on the right side of the TV","Thanks","Oh, and here are your glasses. They were next to your cell phone"]', '["T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng th\\u1ec3 t\\u00ecm th\\u1ea5y c\\u1eb7p ki\\u1ebfng c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i v\\u00e0 t\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng th\\u1ea5y g\\u00ec h\\u1ebft. B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 gi\\u00fap t\\u00f4i t\\u00ecm v\\u00e0i th\\u1ee9 \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 v\\u1ea5n \\u0111\\u1ec1 g\\u00ec. B\\u1ea1n \\u0111ang t\\u00ecm c\\u00e1i g\\u00ec?","M\\u00e1y t\\u00ednh x\\u00e1ch tay c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i, b\\u1ea1n th\\u1ea5y n\\u00f3 kh\\u00f4ng?","C\\u00f3, m\\u00e1y t\\u00ednh c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n \\u1edf tr\\u00ean gh\\u1ebf","Quy\\u1ec3n s\\u00e1ch c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Quy\\u1ec3n s\\u00e1ch n\\u00e0o?","Quy\\u1ec3n t\\u1eeb \\u0111i\\u1ec3n","N\\u00f3 \\u1edf d\\u01b0\\u1edbi c\\u00e1i b\\u00e0n","B\\u00fat ch\\u00ec c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","C\\u00f3 m\\u1ed9t c\\u00e2y vi\\u1ebft ch\\u00ec tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc c\\u00e1i \\u0111\\u00e8n","\\u0110\\u00f3 kh\\u00f4ng ph\\u1ea3i l\\u00e0 vi\\u1ebft ch\\u00ec. \\u0110\\u00f3 l\\u00e0 vi\\u1ebft m\\u1ef1c","\\u00d4, xin l\\u1ed7i. C\\u00f3 m\\u1ed9t c\\u00e2y vi\\u1ebft ch\\u00ec sau c\\u00e1i t\\u00e1ch","C\\u00f2n ba l\\u00f4 c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i th\\u00ec sao? B\\u1ea1n bi\\u1ebft n\\u00f3 \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u kh\\u00f4ng?","N\\u00f3 \\u1edf gi\\u1eefa b\\u1ee9c t\\u01b0\\u1eddng v\\u00e0 gi\\u01b0\\u1eddng ng\\u1ee7","\\u0110\\u00f4i gi\\u00e0y c\\u1ee7a t\\u00f4i \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Ch\\u00fang \\u1edf b\\u00ean tr\\u00e1i c\\u1ee7a c\\u00e1i ti vi","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng tr\\u00f4ng th\\u1ea5y ch\\u00fang","Xin l\\u1ed7i, t\\u00f4i l\\u1ea7m. Ch\\u00fang \\u1edf b\\u00ean ph\\u1ea3i c\\u1ee7a c\\u00e1i ti vi","C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n","\\u00d4, c\\u00f2n \\u0111\\u00e2y l\\u00e0 c\\u1eb7p ki\\u1ebfng c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n. Ch\\u00fang \\u1edf c\\u1ea1nh c\\u00e1i \\u0111i\\u1ec7n tho\\u1ea1i di \\u0111\\u1ed9ng c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n"]', '1', '31', '2017-08-03 20:04:55', '2017-08-03 20:04:55'),
(32, 'Paying for dinner', 'paying-for-dinner', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-32.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/32.mp3', 'Tim', 'Waitress', '["Excuse me. Check please","OK, how was everything?","Very nice. Thank you","Would you like this to-go?","Yes, can you put it in a plastic bag?","Sure, no problem. Here you are. That\\u2019ll be 25 dollars","Do you take credit cards?","Yes, we accept Visa and MasterCard","OK, here you are","Thanks. I\\u2019ll be right back","OK","Here\\u2019s your receipt","Thank you","You\\u2019re welcome. Please come again"]', '["Xin l\\u1ed7i. Cho t\\u00f4i phi\\u1ebfu t\\u00ednh ti\\u1ec1n","V\\u00e2ng \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, m\\u00f3n \\u0103n th\\u1ebf n\\u00e0o?","Ngon l\\u1eafm. C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 mu\\u1ed1n mang v\\u1ec1 m\\u00f3n n\\u00e0y kh\\u00f4ng?","V\\u00e2ng, b\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 b\\u1ecf n\\u00f3 v\\u00e0o m\\u1ed9t c\\u00e1i bao ny l\\u00f4ng kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9, kh\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 v\\u1ea5n \\u0111\\u1ec1 g\\u00ec. C\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e2y. T\\u1ea5t c\\u1ea3 25 \\u0111\\u00f4","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 nh\\u1eadn th\\u1ebb t\\u00edn d\\u1ee5ng kh\\u00f4ng?","C\\u00f3, ch\\u00fang t\\u00f4i nh\\u1eadn th\\u1ebb Visa v\\u00e0 MasterCard","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, \\u0111\\u00e2y","C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n, t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd tr\\u1edf l\\u1ea1i ngay","V\\u00e2ng","\\u0110\\u00e2y l\\u00e0 h\\u00f3a \\u0111\\u01a1n c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n","C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n","Kh\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 g\\u00ec. Mong b\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd tr\\u1edf l\\u1ea1i"]', '1', '32', '2017-08-03 20:17:57', '2017-08-03 20:17:57'),
(33, 'Buying a plane ticket', 'buying-a-plane-ticket', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-33.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/33.mp3', 'Ticket clerk', 'Larry', '["Next please. Hello. How can I help you?","I\\u2019d like to buy a ticket to New York","Would you like one way or round trip?","Round trip","When will you be leaving?","When does the next plane leave?","In about 2 hours","I\\u2019d like a ticket for that flight please","First class or coach?","Coach","OK, let me check availability. I\\u2019m sorry. Tickets for that flight are sold out","How about the one after that?","Let me see. Yes, that one still has seats available. Would you like me to reserve a seat for you?","Yes, please","That\\u2019ll be 120 dollars","OK","Thank you, here\\u2019s your change"]', '["Ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi ti\\u1ebfp theo, l\\u00e0m \\u01a1n. T\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 gi\\u00fap g\\u00ec b\\u1ea1n?","T\\u00f4i mu\\u1ed1n mua m\\u1ed9t v\\u00e9 \\u0111i New York","B\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n v\\u00e9 m\\u1ed9t chi\\u1ec1u hay kh\\u1ee9 h\\u1ed3i?","V\\u00e9 kh\\u1ee9 h\\u1ed3i","B\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd \\u0111i khi n\\u00e0o?","Khi n\\u00e0o th\\u00ec chuy\\u1ebfn bay k\\u1ebf ti\\u1ebfp c\\u1ea5t c\\u00e1nh?","Trong kho\\u1ea3ng 2 gi\\u1edd","T\\u00f4i mu\\u1ed1n m\\u1ed9t v\\u00e9 cho chuy\\u1ebfn bay \\u0111\\u00f3","H\\u1ea1ng nh\\u1ea5t hay h\\u1ea1ng th\\u01b0\\u1eddng?","H\\u1ea1ng th\\u01b0\\u1eddng","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, \\u0111\\u1ec3 t\\u00f4i xem c\\u00f2n v\\u00e9 kh\\u00f4ng. T\\u00f4i r\\u1ea5t ti\\u1ebfc. V\\u00e9 cho chuy\\u1ebfn bay \\u0111\\u00f3 b\\u00e1n h\\u1ebft m\\u1ea5t r\\u1ed3i","C\\u00f2n chuy\\u1ebfn bay k\\u1ebf \\u0111\\u00f3 th\\u00ec sao?","\\u0110\\u1ec3 t\\u00f4i xem. V\\u00e2ng, chuy\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u00f3 c\\u00f2n gh\\u1ebf. B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 mu\\u1ed1n t\\u00f4i d\\u00e0nh s\\u1eb5n cho b\\u1ea1n m\\u1ed9t gh\\u1ebf kh\\u00f4ng?","V\\u00e2ng, l\\u00e0m \\u01a1n","Gi\\u00e1 v\\u00e9 l\\u00e0 120 \\u0111\\u00f4","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c","C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n. Ti\\u1ec1n th\\u1ed1i l\\u1ea1i c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e2y"]', '1', '33', '2017-08-03 20:38:37', '2017-08-03 20:38:37'),
(34, 'Putting things in order', 'putting-things-in-order', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-34.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/34.mp3', 'Frank', 'Michelle', '["Michelle, Can you help me clean things up before we go?","Sure. Where should I put this cup?","Which cup?","The red one","Put it on top of the table","How about this fruit?","Oh, that goes in the refrigerator","And those pencils? What should I do with them?","Bring those upstairs and put them in the bedroom","How about this pen?","Give it to me. I need to use it","What do you want me to do with that paper over there?","You can throw that away. I don\\u2019t need it anymore","The trash is full","Alright, then please put it in a bag and take it outside","OK. Now what?","I think we\\u2019re finished. Can you please turn off the lights and shut the door?","Sure"]', '["Michelle, b\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 gi\\u00fap t\\u00f4i d\\u1ecdn d\\u1eb9p m\\u1ecdi th\\u1ee9 tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc khi ch\\u00fang ta \\u0111i kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9. T\\u00f4i n\\u00ean \\u0111\\u1eb7t c\\u00e1i t\\u00e1ch n\\u00e0y \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","C\\u00e1i t\\u00e1ch n\\u00e0o?","C\\u00e1i \\u0111\\u1ecf","\\u0110\\u1eb7t n\\u00f3 tr\\u00ean m\\u1eb7t b\\u00e0n","C\\u00f2n s\\u1ed1 tr\\u00e1i c\\u00e2y n\\u00e0y","\\u00d4, \\u0111\\u1eb7t ch\\u00fang v\\u00e0o t\\u1ee7 l\\u1ea1nh","V\\u00e0 nh\\u1eefng c\\u00e2y vi\\u1ebft ch\\u00ec n\\u00e0y. T\\u00f4i n\\u00ean l\\u00e0m g\\u00ec v\\u1edbi ch\\u00fang?","Mang ch\\u00fang l\\u00ean l\\u1ea7u v\\u00e0 \\u0111\\u1eb7t ch\\u00fang trong ph\\u00f2ng ng\\u1ee7","C\\u00f2n c\\u00e2y vi\\u1ebft n\\u00e0y?","\\u0110\\u01b0a n\\u00f3 cho t\\u00f4i. T\\u00f4i c\\u1ea7n d\\u00f9ng n\\u00f3","B\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n t\\u00f4i l\\u00e0m g\\u00ec v\\u1edbi t\\u1edd b\\u00e1o \\u1edf \\u0111\\u1eb1ng kia?","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 qu\\u1eb3ng n\\u00f3 \\u0111i. T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng c\\u1ea7n n\\u00f3 n\\u1eefa","Th\\u00f9ng r\\u00e1c \\u0111\\u1ea7y r\\u1ed3i","Th\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, v\\u1eady \\u0111\\u1eb7t n\\u00f3 v\\u00e0o m\\u1ed9t c\\u00e1i bao v\\u00e0 mang ra ngo\\u00e0i","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c r\\u1ed3i. B\\u00e2y gi\\u1edd l\\u00e0m g\\u00ec?","T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 ch\\u00fang ta xong r\\u1ed3i. B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 t\\u1eaft \\u0111\\u00e8n v\\u00e0 \\u0111\\u00f3ng c\\u1eeda \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9"]', '1', '34', '2017-08-03 20:52:22', '2017-08-03 20:52:22'),
(35, 'At the restaurant', 'at-the-restaurant', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-35.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/35.mp3', 'Rebecca', 'Scott', '["This looks like a nice restaurant","Yeah, it is. I come here all the time","Let\\u2019s sit over there","OK","Can you pass me a menu please","Sure. What are you going to have to drink?","I\\u2019m going to have a glass of beer. How about you?","I think I\\u2019ll have a glass of wine","Do you want to order an appetizer first?","Not really, maybe we can just order some bread","OK. What are you going to have to eat?","I\\u2019m not sure. I haven\\u2019t decided yet. Can you recommend something?","Sure, I\\u2019ve had the steak and the lobster before. They\\u2019re both very good","I think I\\u2019ll have the lobster. What are you going to have?","I\\u2019m not that hungry. I think I\\u2019m just going to have a salad","I\\u2019m gonna go to the bathroom. When the waitress comes back, will you order for me?","Sure. No problem"]', '["\\u0110\\u00e2y tr\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 v\\u1ebb m\\u1ed9t nh\\u00e0 h\\u00e0ng ngon \\u0111\\u1ea5y","\\u0110\\u00fang v\\u1eady. T\\u00f4i r\\u1ea5t th\\u01b0\\u1eddng \\u0111\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u00e2y","Ch\\u00fang ta h\\u00e3y ng\\u1ed3i \\u1edf \\u0111\\u1eb1ng kia","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111\\u01b0a t\\u00f4i t\\u1ea5m th\\u1ef1c \\u0111\\u01a1n \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9. B\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd u\\u1ed1ng g\\u00ec?","T\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd u\\u1ed1ng m\\u1ed9t ly bia. C\\u00f2n b\\u1ea1n?","T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd u\\u1ed1ng m\\u1ed9t ly r\\u01b0\\u1ee3u","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 mu\\u1ed1n k\\u00eau m\\u1ed9t m\\u00f3n khai v\\u1ecb tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 mu\\u1ed1n, c\\u00f3 l\\u1ebd ch\\u00fang ta c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 k\\u00eau m\\u1ed9t \\u00edt b\\u00e1nh m\\u00ec","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c. B\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd \\u0103n m\\u00f3n g\\u00ec?","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng ch\\u1eafc. T\\u00f4i ch\\u01b0a quy\\u1ebft \\u0111\\u1ecbnh. B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111\\u1ec1 ngh\\u1ecb m\\u00f3n g\\u00ec kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9. T\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u00e3 \\u0103n m\\u00f3n th\\u1ecbt b\\u00edt t\\u1ebft v\\u00e0 t\\u00f4m h\\u00f9m tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc \\u0111\\u00e2y. C\\u1ea3 hai m\\u00f3n \\u0111\\u1ec1u ngon","T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd \\u0103n t\\u00f4m h\\u00f9m. B\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd \\u0103n m\\u00f3n g\\u00ec?","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng \\u0111\\u00f3i l\\u1eafm. T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 t\\u00f4i ch\\u1ec9 \\u0103n m\\u1ed9t d\\u0129a rau s\\u1ed1ng tr\\u1ed9n d\\u1ea7u gi\\u1ea5m","T\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd v\\u00e0o ph\\u00f2ng v\\u1ec7 sinh. Khi ng\\u01b0\\u1eddi ph\\u1ee5c v\\u1ee5 tr\\u1edf l\\u1ea1i, b\\u1ea1n g\\u1ecdi m\\u00f3n \\u0103n gi\\u00fap t\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9?","D\\u0129 nhi\\u00ean. Kh\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 v\\u1ea5n \\u0111\\u1ec1 g\\u00ec"]', '2', '35', '2017-08-03 21:10:23', '2017-08-03 21:10:23'),
(36, 'I need to do laundry', 'i-need-to-do-laundry', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-36.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/36.mp3', 'Eric', 'Ana', '["Hi Anna, come in","Wow, your apartment is a mess","I know, I didn\\u2019t have time to put things away before you got here","Look! Are those all your clothes on the couch?","Yes","Are they clean?","Actually most of them are dirty. I haven\\u2019t done laundry in a while. I usually wait until I can do it at my parent\\u2019s house","My sister and I usually go to the laundromat down the street. Why don\\u2019t you go there?","I know I should, but that place isn\\u2019t very convenient. You have to wait for a long time","Yes I know. I have to do it every week. Anyway, are you ready to go?","No I\\u2019m not ready yet. I still have to brush my teeth and wash my face. Can you wait for a few minutes?","OK, but please hurry. I think the restaurant is closing soon"]', '["Ch\\u00e0o Anna, v\\u00e0o \\u0111i","\\u1ed2, c\\u0103n h\\u1ed9 b\\u1ea1n b\\u1eeba b\\u00e3i v\\u1eady","T\\u00f4i bi\\u1ebft. T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng c\\u00f3 th\\u1eddi gian c\\u1ea5t m\\u1ecdi th\\u1ee9 \\u0111i tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc khi b\\u1ea1n t\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u00e2y","Xem k\\u00eca! C\\u00f3 ph\\u1ea3i \\u0111\\u00f3 l\\u00e0 qu\\u1ea7n \\u00e1o c\\u1ee7a b\\u1ea1n tr\\u00ean c\\u00e1i \\u0111i v\\u0103ng kh\\u00f4ng?","V\\u00e2ng","Ch\\u00fang c\\u00f3 s\\u1ea1ch kh\\u00f4ng?","S\\u1ef1 th\\u1ef1c th\\u00ec ph\\u1ea7n l\\u1edbn l\\u00e0 \\u0111\\u1ed3 b\\u1ea9n. T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng gi\\u1eb7t qu\\u1ea7n \\u00e1o m\\u1ed9t th\\u1eddi gian r\\u1ed3i. T\\u00f4i th\\u01b0\\u1eddng ch\\u1edd cho t\\u1edbi khi t\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 gi\\u1eb7t ch\\u00fang \\u1edf nh\\u00e0 b\\u1ed1 m\\u1eb9 t\\u00f4i","Ch\\u1ecb (em g\\u00e1i) t\\u00f4i v\\u00e0 t\\u00f4i th\\u01b0\\u1eddng \\u0111i t\\u1edbi ti\\u1ec7m cho thu\\u00ea m\\u00e1y gi\\u1eb7t \\u1edf d\\u01b0\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1eddng. T\\u1ea1i sao b\\u1ea1n kh\\u00f4ng t\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u00f3?","T\\u00f4i bi\\u1ebft t\\u00f4i n\\u00ean t\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u00f3, nh\\u01b0ng n\\u01a1i \\u0111\\u00f3 kh\\u00f4ng ti\\u1ec7n l\\u1ee3i l\\u1eafm. B\\u1ea1n ph\\u1ea3i ch\\u1edd l\\u00e2u","V\\u00e2ng t\\u00f4i bi\\u1ebft. T\\u00f4i ph\\u1ea3i gi\\u1eb7t qu\\u1ea7n \\u00e1o h\\u00e0ng tu\\u1ea7n. D\\u00f9 sao, b\\u1ea1n s\\u1eb5n s\\u00e0ng \\u0111i ch\\u01b0a?","Ch\\u01b0a \\u0111\\u00e2u, t\\u00f4i ch\\u01b0a s\\u1eb5n s\\u00e0ng \\u0111i. T\\u00f4i c\\u00f2n ph\\u1ea3i \\u0111\\u00e1nh r\\u0103ng v\\u00e0 r\\u1eeda m\\u1eb7t. B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 ch\\u1edd v\\u00e0i ph\\u00fat \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, nh\\u01b0ng l\\u00e0m \\u01a1n nhanh l\\u00ean. T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 nh\\u00e0 h\\u00e0ng s\\u1eafp \\u0111\\u00f3ng c\\u1eeda r\\u1ed3i"]', '2', '36', '2017-08-03 21:30:30', '2017-08-03 21:30:30'),
(37, 'Finding a convenience store', 'finding-a-convenience-store', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-37.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/37.mp3', 'Andrew', 'Pam', '["Pam, where\\u2019s the closest ATM?","It\\u2019s not that far. Do you see that Yellow building over there?","The big one or the small one?","The big one","Yes","It\\u2019s right next to it, on the right","Do you know if there\\u2019s a convenience store around here?","I don\\u2019t think there\\u2019s one around here. The closest one is on 3rd street, but that\\u2019s probably closed now","I really need to get some things before I leave","Well, you could go down to 22nd street. There are lot of stores down there that are open 24 hours a day","Can I take the subway to get there?","Yes, but that\\u2019ll probably take about half an hour. You should just take a cab","Won\\u2019t that be expensive?","No, from here I think it\\u2019s only about 5 dollars"]', '["Pam, m\\u00e1y ATM g\\u1ea7n \\u0111\\u00e2y nh\\u1ea5t \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Kh\\u00f4ng xa \\u0111\\u00e2u. B\\u1ea1n th\\u1ea5y t\\u00f2a nh\\u00e0 v\\u00e0ng \\u0111\\u1eb1ng kia kh\\u00f4ng?","T\\u00f2a nh\\u00e0 l\\u1edbn hay nh\\u1ecf?","T\\u00f2a nh\\u00e0 l\\u1edbn","C\\u00f3","N\\u00f3 \\u1edf ngay b\\u00ean c\\u1ea1nh, ph\\u00eda b\\u00ean ph\\u1ea3i","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 bi\\u1ebft c\\u00f3 m\\u1ed9t c\\u1eeda h\\u00e0ng ti\\u1ec7n l\\u1ee3i g\\u1ea7n \\u0111\\u00e2y kh\\u00f4ng?","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng ngh\\u0129 l\\u00e0 c\\u00f3 m\\u1ed9t c\\u1eeda h\\u00e0ng g\\u1ea7n \\u0111\\u00e2y. C\\u1eeda h\\u00e0ng g\\u1ea7n nh\\u1ea5t \\u1edf tr\\u00ean \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1eddng th\\u1ee9 3, nh\\u01b0ng gi\\u1edd n\\u00e0y c\\u00f3 l\\u1ebd \\u0111\\u00f3ng c\\u1eeda r\\u1ed3i","T\\u00f4i th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 c\\u1ea7n mua m\\u1ed9t v\\u00e0i m\\u00f3n tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc khi t\\u00f4i \\u0111i","\\u1ed2, b\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111i xu\\u1ed1ng \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1eddng th\\u1ee9 22. C\\u00f3 nhi\\u1ec1u c\\u1eeda h\\u00e0ng \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00f3 m\\u1edf c\\u1eeda 24 gi\\u1edd m\\u1ed9t ng\\u00e0y","T\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111i xe \\u0111i\\u1ec7n ng\\u1ea7m t\\u1edbi \\u0111\\u00f3 \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, nh\\u01b0ng nh\\u01b0 v\\u1eady m\\u1ea5t kho\\u1ea3ng n\\u1eeda ti\\u1ebfng. B\\u1ea1n n\\u00ean \\u0111i t\\u1eafc xi","\\u0110i nh\\u01b0 v\\u1eady kh\\u00f4ng \\u0111\\u1eaft sao?","Kh\\u00f4ng, t\\u1eeb \\u0111\\u00e2y t\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 ch\\u1ec9 t\\u1ed1n kho\\u1ea3ng 5 \\u0111\\u00f4"]', '2', '37', '2017-08-03 21:37:48', '2017-08-03 21:37:48'),
(38, 'Lesson: 38 Geography and direction', 'lesson-38-geography-and-direction', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-38.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/38.mp3', 'Mandy', 'Professor', '["Professor, where\\u2019s Canada?","Canada is north of here","Can you show me on the map?","Sure. Look here. Canada is north of the United States","Oh, I see. Where\\u2019s Mexico?","Mexico is south of the United States","How about Connecticut? Where\\u2019s that?","Connecticut is east of New York","What state is west of Pennsylvania?","Ohio","OK, Where\\u2019s Los Angeles?","Los Angeles is in California. It\\u2019s southeast of San Francisco","Where\\u2019s Boston","Boston is in the northeast part of the country","Where is Las Vegas?","Las Vegas is in the southwest"]', '["Th\\u01b0a gi\\u00e1o s\\u01b0, Canada \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Canada \\u1edf ph\\u00eda b\\u1eafc c\\u1ee7a n\\u01a1i n\\u00e0y","Th\\u00e0y c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 ch\\u1ec9 cho t\\u00f4i tr\\u00ean b\\u1ea3n \\u0111\\u1ed3 \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c ch\\u1ee9. Xem \\u0111\\u00e2y. Canada \\u1edf ph\\u00eda b\\u1eafc c\\u1ee7a n\\u01b0\\u1edbc M\\u1ef9","\\u00d4, t\\u00f4i th\\u1ea5y r\\u1ed3i. Mexico \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Mexico \\u1edf ph\\u00eda nam c\\u1ee7a n\\u01b0\\u1edbc M\\u1ef9","C\\u00f2n Connecticut? N\\u01a1i \\u0111\\u00f3 \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Connecticut \\u1edf ph\\u00eda \\u0111\\u00f4ng c\\u1ee7a New York","Bang n\\u00e0o \\u1edf ph\\u00eda t\\u00e2y c\\u1ee7a Pennsylvania?","Ohio","V\\u00e2ng. Los Angeles \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Los Angeles \\u1edf California. N\\u00f3 \\u1edf ph\\u00eda \\u0111\\u00f4ng nam c\\u1ee7a San Francisco","Boston \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Boston \\u1edf mi\\u1ec1n \\u0111\\u00f4ng b\\u1eafc c\\u1ee7a \\u0111\\u1ea5t n\\u01b0\\u1edbc","Las Vegas \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00e2u?","Las Vegas \\u1edf ph\\u00eda t\\u00e2y nam"]', '2', '38', '2017-08-03 21:43:47', '2017-08-03 21:43:47'),
(39, 'I ate at the hotel', 'i-ate-at-the-hotel', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-39.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/39.mp3', 'Ray', 'Maria', '["Hi Maria, did you have breakfast yet?","Yes, I ate at the hotel with my son and my husband","Oh, they have good food there. What did you have?","I had some cereal, fried eggs and orange juice","How was it?","The food didn\\u2019t taste very good, and actually I don\\u2019t feel very well now","That\\u2019s too bad. Do you want to take a break?","No, I\\u2019m going to go back to the hotel at lunch time to lie down","OK. I\\u2019m going to the drug store later. Is there anything I can get for you?","No, that\\u2019s OK. I think if I rest for a little while I\\u2019ll feel better"]', '["Ch\\u00e0o Maria, b\\u1ea1n \\u0103n s\\u00e1ng ch\\u01b0a?","V\\u00e2ng, t\\u00f4i \\u0103n \\u1edf kh\\u00e1ch s\\u1ea1n v\\u1edbi con trai v\\u00e0 ch\\u1ed3ng t\\u00f4i","\\u00d4, \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00f3 h\\u1ecd c\\u00f3 th\\u1ee9c \\u0103n ngon. B\\u1ea1n d\\u00f9ng m\\u00f3n g\\u00ec?","T\\u00f4i d\\u00f9ng ng\\u0169 c\\u1ed1c, tr\\u1ee9ng chi\\u00ean v\\u00e0 n\\u01b0\\u1edbc cam v\\u1eaft","M\\u1ea5y m\\u00f3n \\u0111\\u00f3 th\\u1ebf n\\u00e0o?","Th\\u1ee9c \\u0103n kh\\u00f4ng ngon l\\u1eafm, th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 l\\u00e0 b\\u00e2y gi\\u1edd t\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng c\\u1ea3m th\\u1ea5y kh\\u1ecfe l\\u1eafm","T\\u1ec7 qu\\u00e1. B\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n ngh\\u1ec9 m\\u1ed9t l\\u00fac kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng. T\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd tr\\u1edf l\\u1ea1i kh\\u00e1ch s\\u1ea1n v\\u00e0o gi\\u1edd \\u0103n tr\\u01b0a \\u0111\\u1ec3 n\\u1eb1m ngh\\u1ec9","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c. L\\u00e1t n\\u1eefa t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd \\u0111i t\\u1edbi ti\\u1ec7m thu\\u1ed1c t\\u00e2y. T\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 mua cho b\\u1ea1n th\\u1ee9 g\\u00ec kh\\u00f4ng?","Kh\\u00f4ng, \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c th\\u00f4i. T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 l\\u00e0 n\\u1ebfu t\\u00f4i ngh\\u1ec9 m\\u1ed9t l\\u00fac t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd c\\u1ea3m th\\u1ea5y kh\\u1ecfe h\\u01a1n"]', '2', '39', '2017-08-03 21:53:09', '2017-08-03 21:53:09'),
(40, 'Going to the movies', 'going-to-the-movies', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-40.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/40.mp3', 'Jerry', 'Ann', '["Ann what do you want to do tonight?","I\\u2019d like to go see a movie","I heard Titanic is playing at the movie theater","Oh, I\\u2019ve heard that\\u2019s a good movie. What time does it start?","6:30PM. It\\u2019s a long movie. I think it lasts for about 3 hours","Will you come and pick me up?","What time?","I think we should get there early because they might be sold out. Is 5:00PM OK?","Yes, that\\u2019ll be fine. I\\u2019ll meet you at your house at 5:00PM","Do you want to get something to eat before the movie?","I\\u2019m not sure there will be enough time for that. We can have popcorn and hot dogs at the theater if you want","I don\\u2019t like the popcorn they have there. I think they put too much salt on it","OK then, I\\u2019ll pick you up a little earlier and we can go to the Thai restaurant next to the theater, is that OK?","Yes, I like that place"]', '["Ann, b\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n l\\u00e0m g\\u00ec t\\u1ed1i nay?","T\\u00f4i mu\\u1ed1n \\u0111i xem phim","T\\u00f4i nghe n\\u00f3i phim Titanic \\u0111ang chi\\u1ebfu \\u1edf r\\u1ea1p","\\u00d4, t\\u00f4i nghe n\\u00f3i \\u0111\\u00f3 l\\u00e0 m\\u1ed9t b\\u1ed9 phim hay. M\\u1ea5y gi\\u1edd n\\u00f3 b\\u1eaft \\u0111\\u1ea7u?","6:30 t\\u1ed1i. \\u0110\\u00f3 l\\u00e0 m\\u1ed9t b\\u1ed9 phim d\\u00e0i. T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 n\\u00f3 d\\u00e0i kho\\u1ea3ng 3 ti\\u1ebfng","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u00f3n t\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","M\\u1ea5y gi\\u1edd?","T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 ch\\u00fang ta n\\u00ean \\u0111\\u1ebfn \\u0111\\u00f3 s\\u1edbm v\\u00ec h\\u1ecd c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 b\\u00e1n h\\u1ebft v\\u00e9. 5:00 gi\\u1edd chi\\u1ec1u \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, nh\\u01b0 v\\u1eady t\\u1ed1t r\\u1ed3i. T\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd \\u0111\\u00f3n b\\u1ea1n \\u1edf nh\\u00e0 b\\u1ea1n l\\u00fac 5:00 gi\\u1edd chi\\u1ec1u","B\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 mu\\u1ed1n mua g\\u00ec \\u0111\\u1ec3 \\u0103n tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc khi xem phim kh\\u00f4ng?","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng ngh\\u0129 c\\u00f3 \\u0111\\u1ee7 th\\u1eddi gian cho vi\\u1ec7c \\u0111\\u00f3. Ch\\u00fang ta c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0103n ng\\u00f4 rang v\\u00e0 b\\u00e1nh m\\u00ec x\\u00fac x\\u00edch t\\u1ea1i r\\u1ea1p chi\\u1ebfu phim n\\u1ebfu b\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n","T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng th\\u00edch ng\\u00f4 rang h\\u1ecd b\\u00e1n \\u1edf \\u0111\\u00f3. T\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 h\\u1ecd b\\u1ecf nhi\\u1ec1u mu\\u1ed1i qu\\u00e1","Th\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c. T\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd \\u0111\\u00f3n b\\u1ea1n s\\u1edbm h\\u01a1n m\\u1ed9t ch\\u00fat v\\u00e0 ch\\u00fang ta c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 \\u0111i \\u0111\\u1ebfn nh\\u00e0 h\\u00e0ng Th\\u00e1i b\\u00ean c\\u1ea1nh r\\u1ea1p chi\\u1ebfu phim. Nh\\u01b0 v\\u1eady \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","V\\u00e2ng, t\\u00f4i th\\u00edch n\\u01a1i \\u0111\\u00f3"]', '2', '40', '2017-08-03 23:34:12', '2017-08-03 23:34:12'),
(41, 'The food tastes great', 'the-food-tastes-great', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-41.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/41.mp3', 'Patrick', 'Diane', '["How do you like the food?","It tastes really great. Did you cook it?","Yes. I made it this afternoon. Would you like some more?","OK, just a little though. I\\u2019m really full","Oh. Would you like some soup instead?","What kind is it?","Tomato and rice. Have you had that before?","No. This is my first time. How does it taste?","It\\u2019s good, try it. What do you think?","Wow. It is good. Did you make that also?","Yes","You\\u2019re a really good cook","Thanks, next time I\\u2019ll make chicken soup for us","That sounds good. Did you study cooking in school?","No, I learned by myself. I have a good cook book that I read when I have time"]', '["B\\u1ea1n th\\u00edch m\\u00f3n \\u0103n l\\u1eafm kh\\u00f4ng?","N\\u00f3 r\\u1ea5t ngon. B\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e3 n\\u1ea5u m\\u00f3n \\u0111\\u00f3 h\\u1ea3?","V\\u00e2ng, t\\u00f4i n\\u1ea5u h\\u1ed3i chi\\u1ec1u nay. B\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n \\u0103n th\\u00eam kh\\u00f4ng?","V\\u00e2ng, nh\\u01b0ng ch\\u1ec9 m\\u1ed9t \\u00edt th\\u00f4i. T\\u00f4i th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 no r\\u1ed3i","\\u00d4. B\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n m\\u1ed9t \\u00edt x\\u00fap thay v\\u00e0o \\u0111\\u00f3 kh\\u00f4ng?","Lo\\u1ea1i x\\u00fap g\\u00ec?","C\\u00e0 chua v\\u00e0 g\\u1ea1o. B\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e3 \\u0103n m\\u00f3n \\u0111\\u00f3 tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc \\u0111\\u00e2y ch\\u01b0a","Ch\\u01b0a. \\u0110\\u00e2y l\\u00e0 l\\u1ea7n \\u0111\\u1ea7u. N\\u00f3 c\\u00f3 v\\u1ecb ra sao?","Ngon, th\\u1eed xem. B\\u1ea1n ngh\\u0129 sao?","\\u00d4. N\\u00f3 ngon l\\u1eafm. B\\u1ea1n c\\u0169ng \\u0111\\u00e3 l\\u00e0m m\\u00f3n n\\u00e0y h\\u1ea3?","V\\u00e2ng","B\\u1ea1n th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 l\\u00e0 m\\u1ed9t \\u0111\\u1ea7u b\\u1ebfp gi\\u1ecfi","C\\u00e1m \\u01a1n, l\\u1ea7n t\\u1edbi t\\u00f4i s\\u1ebd l\\u00e0m m\\u00f3n x\\u00fap g\\u00e0 cho ch\\u00fang ta","Nghe hay \\u0111\\u1ea5y. B\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e3 h\\u1ecdc n\\u1ea5u \\u0103n trong tr\\u01b0\\u1eddng h\\u1ea3?","Kh\\u00f4ng, t\\u00f4i t\\u1ef1 h\\u1ecdc. T\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 m\\u1ed9t quy\\u1ec3n s\\u00e1ch d\\u1ea1y n\\u1ea5u \\u0103n t\\u1ed1t t\\u00f4i v\\u1eabn \\u0111\\u1ecdc khi c\\u00f3 th\\u1eddi gian"]', '2', '41', '2017-08-03 23:41:14', '2017-08-03 23:41:14'),
(42, 'Helping a friend move', 'helping-a-friend-move', '/uploads/images/lesson/images/lesson-42.jpg', '/uploads/Audio/lesson/audio/42.mp3', 'Peter', 'Kelly', '["Kelly, will you help me take these things to the car?","OK, which car do you want me to put them in?","Bring them to my wife\\u2019s car","Which one is hers\\u2019?","The blue SUV in front of the Honda","What should I take first?","That chair over there, but please be careful with it. It was a gift from my mother-in-law","Don\\u2019t worry, I won\\u2019t drop it. Wow, it\\u2019s really heavy. I don\\u2019t think I can move it by myself","Let me help you with that. I don\\u2019t want you to hurt your back","Where are you taking all this stuff?","Didn\\u2019t I tell you? We\\u2019re moving to Florida?","You\\u2019re moving now? I knew you were moving, but I thought you said you were moving next month","Yes, that\\u2019s true, but my wife found a new apartment on the Internet the other day and she wants to move right away"]', '["Kelly, b\\u1ea1n c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 gi\\u00fap t\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0a m\\u1ea5y th\\u1ee9 n\\u00e0y ra xe \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c kh\\u00f4ng?","\\u0110\\u01b0\\u1ee3c, b\\u1ea1n mu\\u1ed1n t\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u1eb7t ch\\u00fang v\\u00e0o xe n\\u00e0o?","\\u0110\\u01b0a ch\\u00fang ra xe c\\u1ee7a v\\u1ee3 t\\u00f4i","Xe n\\u00e0o c\\u1ee7a b\\u00e0 \\u1ea5y?","Chi\\u1ebfc SUV xanh tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc chi\\u1ebfc Honda","T\\u00f4i n\\u00ean mang th\\u1ee9 g\\u00ec tr\\u01b0\\u1edbc?","Chi\\u1ebfc gh\\u1ebf \\u1edf \\u0111\\u1eb1ng kia, nh\\u01b0ng l\\u00e0m \\u01a1n c\\u1ea9n th\\u1eadn. N\\u00f3 l\\u00e0 m\\u1ed9t m\\u00f3n qu\\u00e0 t\\u1eeb m\\u1eb9 v\\u1ee3 t\\u00f4i","\\u0110\\u1eebng lo, t\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng \\u0111\\u00e1nh r\\u01a1i n\\u00f3 \\u0111\\u00e2u. \\u00d4i, n\\u00f3 th\\u1ef1c s\\u1ef1 l\\u00e0 n\\u1eb7ng. T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng ngh\\u0129 r\\u1eb1ng t\\u00f4i c\\u00f3 th\\u1ec3 chuy\\u1ec3n n\\u00f3 \\u0111i t\\u1ef1 m\\u1ed9t m\\u00ecnh t\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c","\\u0110\\u1ec3 t\\u00f4i gi\\u00fap b\\u1ea1n. T\\u00f4i kh\\u00f4ng mu\\u1ed1n b\\u1ea1n b\\u1ecb \\u0111au l\\u01b0ng","B\\u1ea1n mang t\\u1ea5t c\\u1ea3 m\\u1ea5y th\\u1ee9 n\\u00e0y \\u0111i \\u0111\\u00e2u?","T\\u00f4i \\u0111\\u00e3 kh\\u00f4ng n\\u00f3i v\\u1edbi b\\u1ea1n h\\u1ea3? Ch\\u00fang t\\u00f4i chuy\\u1ec3n \\u0111i Florida","B\\u1ea1n chuy\\u1ec3n \\u0111i b\\u00e2y gi\\u1edd sao? T\\u00f4i bi\\u1ebft l\\u00e0 b\\u1ea1n s\\u1eafp chuy\\u1ec3n \\u0111i, nh\\u01b0ng t\\u00f4i ngh\\u0129 b\\u1ea1n \\u0111\\u00e3 n\\u00f3i l\\u00e0 b\\u1ea1n s\\u1ebd chuy\\u1ec3n \\u0111i v\\u00e0o th\\u00e1ng t\\u1edbi","V\\u00e2ng, \\u0111\\u00fang v\\u1eady, nh\\u01b0ng v\\u1ee3 t\\u00f4i t\\u00ecm \\u0111\\u01b0\\u1ee3c m\\u1ed9t c\\u0103n h\\u1ed9 m\\u1edbi tr\\u00ean Internet m\\u1ed9t ng\\u00e0y n\\u1ecd v\\u00e0 b\\u00e0 \\u1ea5y mu\\u1ed1n chuy\\u1ec3n \\u0111i ngay"]', '2', '42', '2017-08-03 23:46:35', '2017-08-03 23:46:35');
